              <a><a/><p><font color = "white">Mars has dust storms that can cover the entire planet for a whole month, damaging equipment and making travel extremely difficult. Solutions to protecting equipment and moving from place to place need to be developed. 
The dust is made up primarily of oxidized iron and caustic salts is typical of the soil on Mars. Heavy dust storms occur more frequently in the winter than the summer.   These Martian dust storms are the biggest in the solar system, so intense that they can cover the entire planet. This massive blanket of dust, sometimes lasting as long as 30 days or more are so large, they can even be witnessed with by telescope on Earth.</font> </p>

